Pursue the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to finally establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability.

In view of the foregoing, we recommended that Management:
Explain/justify the charging of unrelated expenditures to the Engineering Administrative Overhead and why should it not be disallowed in audit;
Stop the practice of utilizing EAO for expenses not related to the pre-construction and implementation of infrastructure projects, and limit the charging of expenditure against EAO funds to those enumerated under items (i) to (vi) as provided in the DPWH Department Order;
Ensure that only expenses incurred during the project implementation period are capitalized, while post-completion expenses are charged appropriately as operating expenses; and
Implement project-specific monitoring reports to ensure the accuracy, validity, and proper allocation of expenses charged to the Engineering and Administrative Overhead.

